                <h1>Understanding the History of Medicare</h1>
                <p>Medicare, established in 1965 under President Lyndon B. Johnson, revolutionized healthcare for seniors and certain disabled individuals in the U.S. It aimed to provide affordable access to medical services. Over the years, Medicare has evolved, incorporating various parts and plans to adapt to changing healthcare needs and improve coverage.</p>
